{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04039/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04039"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:40:39"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man watches as a woman fixes the dress on a model posing in the background."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04039","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04039"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1/cfaa6b47-bbab-48e5-8a6c-28bbe7eb9ca7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:14:51.963Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This shot underscores the significant role of the characters’ gazes. Here, viewers see Alma from over Reynolds’s shoulder, the camera thus providing them with Reynolds’s perspective. Although she is ostensibly the subject of the shot, she remains out of focus, while Reynolds does not. This choice signifies his dominance in the relationship. On the one hand, the film may be read as commentary on the male gaze and the male artist’s point of view in which women (Alma) are but figures to be manipulated. By the end, however, this perspective will be subverted when Alma takes control, therefore revealing an entirely different possible interpretive level.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04039/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:509.07133243606995,72.92059219380906,682.207267833109,553.0013458950202"}}}]}]}]}